Schools were set to open for Grades 12 and 7 on Monday. JOHANNESBURG - There will be no school on Monday. Instead, Grade 7s and 12s will return to school on 8 June. The Council of Education Ministers says the decision was taken, following a meeting with stakeholders on Saturday. READ: Reopening of schools: Dates announced for other grades Meanwhile, the Western Cape says it is prepared to open schools on 1 June. Basic Education, Angie Motshekga is expected to brief the nation on Monday, 1 June. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.